WEBVTT

00:00.360 --> 00:03.280
Just to be facetious for a second,

00:05.160 --> 00:07.960
let's just introduce an artificial await here.

00:08.840 --> 00:10.440
And I can never remember how to write this off

00:10.440 --> 00:12.960
the top of my head, so I'm gonna ask Coppola to do it.

00:12.960 --> 00:16.360
Wait here for 10 seconds.

00:16.360 --> 00:18.520
It creates a new promise, it waits it for 10 seconds,

00:18.520 --> 00:21.040
then after 10 seconds it resolves it.

00:21.040 --> 00:22.360
So now if you look at this,

00:22.360 --> 00:24.960
it's gonna be empty for the first 10 seconds, right?

00:26.120 --> 00:28.040
Cause it got the information back

00:28.040 --> 00:29.440
cause it's all local host, right?

00:29.440 --> 00:31.480
So it's all instantaneous.

00:31.480 --> 00:33.360
And then after that while it comes back

00:33.360 --> 00:37.880
and then it will finally set the thing to be what you need.

00:40.560 --> 00:41.480
Make sense?

00:44.480 --> 00:45.840
All right.

00:47.040 --> 00:50.320
So that is our fetch pizza, that's our effect.

00:50.320 --> 00:52.760
That's probably the most interesting part of this.

