02:12.080 --> 02:14.680
Notice that now every time that I click this,

02:17.560 --> 02:20.680
I'm getting another Ajax request to the API, right?

02:20.680 --> 02:23.720
Because it's just watching to see whenever that changes.

02:23.720 --> 02:26.600
But notice if I change this, let me trash this

02:26.600 --> 02:27.440
so you can see.

02:31.240 --> 02:33.160
Not doing it, right?

02:33.160 --> 02:35.360
Because we're not changing based on pizza type.

02:35.360 --> 02:37.400
We're only changing based on pizza size.

02:43.760 --> 02:47.640
And if you wanted to change, if anything changes,

02:48.640 --> 02:51.520
give it no array and it's gonna get real mad

02:51.520 --> 02:54.120
and notice that DDoS yourself, right?

02:54.120 --> 02:56.560
Why am I DDoSing it myself?

02:57.520 --> 02:59.080
Because it's re-rendering a lot, right?

03:00.920 --> 03:03.680
Look at my API here, it's just going hog wild.

03:06.320 --> 03:07.520
Oh my God, please stop.

03:11.120 --> 03:14.240
All right, so why is it doing that?

03:14.240 --> 03:15.640
What am I doing right here?

03:17.040 --> 03:20.680
I'm changing the state, which causes a re-render,

03:20.680 --> 03:23.920
which schedules an effect, which changes the state,

03:23.920 --> 03:25.680
which schedules an effect, which changes the state,

03:25.680 --> 03:27.320
which schedules an effect, right?

03:30.000 --> 03:30.840
That's why.

03:32.240 --> 03:33.920
So if you find yourself doing something like that,

03:33.920 --> 03:35.960
you probably forgot an array somewhere.

03:39.320 --> 03:43.720
A general useful rule of thumb is if inside of your effect,

03:43.720 --> 03:46.600
you refer to a piece of state,

03:46.600 --> 03:50.040
it should probably be tracked inside of your,

03:50.960 --> 03:53.080
they call this your dependencies, right?

03:53.080 --> 03:54.320
Your dependent state.

